Before the game, Ball State players wore red T-shirts with Loveâs jersey number 86&nbsp;on the front during warmups, and had stickers with the number on the back of their helmets. A âWe Love Danteâ sign was draped over the fence just past the north end zone and Love also was named an honorary captain. MiQuale Lewis opened the scoring with a two yard touchdown run in the first quarter. Early in the second quarter, Nate Davis threw a pass to Myles Trempe for a 31&nbsp;yard touchdown that gave the Cardinals a 14â0 lead. Kent State responded late in the quarter when quarterback Julian Edelman scored on a 12&nbsp;yard run to cut Ball Stateâs lead to 14â7. Lewis scored his second touchdown on a one yard run with 21&nbsp;seconds left in the second quarter to give the Cardinals a 21â7 lead at halftime. Cory Sykesâ 10&nbsp;yard touchdown run in the opening minutes of the third quarter made it 28â7, and the Cardinals led by at least 17&nbsp;points the rest of the way. Lewis ran for 116&nbsp;yards and three touchdowns and Davis passed for 265&nbsp;yards and a touchdown.<ref>{{cite web | last =Brunt | first =Cliff | title =Ball State beats Kent State without injured Love | publisher =Rivals.com from Yahoo! Sports | date =2008-09-27 | url =http://rivals.yahoo.com/ncaa/football/recap?gid=200809270048 | accessdate =2008-09-29 }}</ref>
