===Miami (OH)=== {{Linescore Amfootball| |Road='''Cardinals''' |R1=0 |R2=17 |R3=7 |R4=7 |Home=RedHawks |H1=0 |H2=13 |H3=3 |H4=0 }}
Nate Davis threw for a touchdown and ran for another, and the Cardinals stayed unbeaten by wearing down the Miami RedHawks for a 31â16&nbsp;victory. Ball State improved to 10â0 for the first time and matched their school record for victories. MiQuale Lewis had two one yard touchdowns in the second half and finished with 165&nbsp;yards, one short of his career high. He also caught two passes for 51&nbsp;yards. For the third straight game, the Cardinals did not draw a penalty.<ref>{{cite news | last =Kay | first =Joe | title =No. 14 Ball St. improves to 10-0 with 31-16 win | agency =Associated Press | date =2008-11-11 | url =http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5hiY3db6pE7c6PvMfFceFlPJIq7NgD94D4IJO0 | accessdate =2008-11-19 }}</ref> Despite the victory, The Cardinals dropped three spots to #17&nbsp;in the BCS Poll, but stayed in the same spot in the Associated Press and ''USA Today'' coaches poll.<ref>{{cite web | title =FOOTBALL: Cards slip in new BCS Standings | publisher =''Ball State Daily News'' | date =2008-11-16 | url =http://media.www.bsudailynews.com/media/storage/paper849/news/2008/11/14/Sports/Football.Cards.Slip.In.New.Bcs.Standings-3545648.shtml | accessdate =2008-11-19 }}</ref>
