===Western Michigan=== {{see also|2008 Western Michigan Broncos football team}} {{Linescore Amfootball| |Road=Broncos |R1=7 |R2=7 |R3=0 |R4=8 |Home='''Cardinals''' |H1=14 |H2=10 |H3=14 |H4=7 }}
MiQuale Lewis started the scoring in the game as he ran for a 10&nbsp;yard touchdown run. On Ball State's next series, Davis completed a 40&nbsp;yard touchdown pass to Lewis Johnson, whose "stop-and-go" move enabled him to elude two defenders. Western Michigan responded with a trick play, scoring when [[Tim Hiller]] threw a [[Lateral pass|lateral]] to backup quarterback Drew Burdi, who turned and threw a 36&nbsp;yard touchdown pass to Scneider Julien, making it 14â7. The Broncos tied it early in the second quarter on a pass from Hiller to Juan Nunez, who caught the nine yard pass over his shoulder. The Cardinals broke the tie on a 43&nbsp;yard field goal from Ian McGarvey and took a 24â14 halftime lead when Davis ran for a six yard touchdown run. Lewis' one yard touchdown run late in the third quarter and Trey Lewis' interception return made it 38â14. Western Michigan closed to 38â22 early in the fourth when Brandon West scored on an eight yard touchdown run. But Lewis closed it out with a one yard touchdown run with 4:31 to go, his twentieth rushing score of the season, which broke the previous record set by Mark Bornholdt in 1979. The Cardinals completed their first perfect regular season since 1949, their first undefeated season in Mid-American Conference play since 1978 and clinched a spot in the conference title game.<ref name="SPB"/> The win gave Ball State its first Mid-American Conference West title in program history.<ref name="FTI"/> A school record 11,088&nbsp;students and 23,861&nbsp;overall attended the game.<ref name="SPB">{{cite news | last =Marot | first =Michael | title =Still perfect: Ball State beats Western Michigan | agency =Associated Press | date =2008-11-25 | url =http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5h2m_-nqw5CWRofv5IwSM5-LJ3xQgD94MCDNO0 | accessdate =2008-11-26 }}</ref><ref name="FTI">{{cite web | title =Football Team Improves to 12-0, Wins MAC West Title | publisher =Ball State Athletics | date =2008-11-25 | url =http://ballstatesports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=67657&SPID=7633&DB_OEM_ID=14200&ATCLID=3623147 | accessdate =2008-11-26 }}</ref> The Cardinals moved up to #12 in the BCS and Associated Press poll and up to #13 in the ''USA Today'' coaches poll.<ref>{{cite web | title =Football Team 12th in BCS and AP; 13th in USA Today | publisher =Ball State Athletics | date =2008-12-06 | url =http://ballstatesports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=67657&SPID=7633&DB_OEM_ID=14200&ATCLID=3625486 | accessdate =2008-12-06 }}</ref>
